main event: A man saw a bright, pinkish-gray-greenish object moving erratically and rapidly across the sky near Richland Center, Wisconsin in 1957.
interesting points: The object made no sound and appeared to disappear and reappear.
The object moved behind and in front of clouds during the sighting.
The witness estimated the object was moving at a very fast speed, around 600-700 mph.
The witness compared the brightness of the object to a bright star.
The sighting lasted for about 20-25 minutes.
